Check out our FAQs for more details.

Population

With 2,289 people, Enterprise city is the 120th most populated city in the state of Utah out of 329 cities. But watch out, Enterprise city, because Willard with 2,283 people and Marriott-Slaterville with 2,223 people are right behind you.

Race & Ethnicity

The largest Enterprise city racial/ethnic groups is White (100.0%)

Median Income

In 2022, the median household income of Enterprise city households was $69,083. Enterprise city households made slightly more than Oak City households ($69,075) and Loa households ($69,063) . However, 0.0% of Enterprise city families live in poverty.

Median Age

The median age for Enterprise city residents is 31.6 years young.
